SUMMARY:The Glass Menagerie
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Season at Curtain Call Theatre starts off with The Glass Menagerie\, the play that made Tennessee Williams famous. \nHave You Ever Felt Stuck Between Your Dreams and Reality? This Play Gets It. \nImagine being trapped in a tiny apartment during the Great Depression — no money\, no way out\, just a family clinging to hopes that may never come true. That’s exactly what The Glass Menagerie is about. \nWritten by Tennessee Williams — one of America’s greatest playwrights — this story follows a restless son\, an overbearing mom\, and a painfully shy daughter as they each chase dreams that feel just out of reach. It’s emotional\, poetic\, and honestly… kind of hits different when you think about your own life. \nThis iconic play is literally studied in classrooms worldwide\, so seeing it live is like watching your textbook come to life — except way more powerful. \nMarch 13–29\, 2026\n20347 Hwy 116\, Monte Rio\, CA\nGrab your tickets at russianriverhall.com or call (707) 387-5072.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/the-glass-menagerie-4/
LOCATION:Curtain Call Theatre\, 20347 Hwy 116\, Monte Rio\, CA
CATEGORIES:Theater
GEO:38.468436;-123.009072
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Curtain Call Theatre 20347 Hwy 116 Monte Rio CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=20347 Hwy 116:geo:-123.009072,38.468436
END:VEVENT
