UID:10016792-1774112400-1774119600@golocal.coop
SUMMARY:Two Painters in the Garden: Alina Nuebel and Frances McCormack
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the opening reception for this spring art show in the Alley Gallery\, a rich and varied exhibition of work by two accomplished Sonoma artists who distill the essence of the natural world through bold and semi-abstract interpretations of trees\, lichens\, birds’ nests\, and more. Alina Nuebel trained as a biologist and brings a scientist’s eye to her fresh and direct observation of the flora and fauna of Sonoma County. Frances McCormack\, a long-time faculty member of the San Francisco Art Institute\, uses vivid color and bold brush strokes to convey the strong currents of energy that run through all living things and burst out to be visible in the woodlands — and in our own gardens.\nThe show runs from March 19-29\, Thursday through Sunday from 12-4 pm. The show and opening reception are free and open to the public.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/two-painters-in-the-garden-alina-nuebel-and-frances-mccormack/
LOCATION:Alley Gallery\, 148 E. Napa St.\, SONOMA\, CA\, 95476\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Twopainters.jpg
END:VEVENT
